description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for Registered Nurses with excellent team working skills to join the Neath Port Talbot District Nursing Team. There is currently a full time post available within team. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful applicant will provide professional, holistic nursing care and support to patients , carers and families within the community setting, delivered with compassion, dignity and respect. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This post will require an individual who delivers the highest quality care, ensuring evidence based/ best practice and has a commitment to continuous professional development. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applications are invited from registrants with excellent communication skills, who have a flexible and adaptable approach to changing work patterns. Hours of work are between 08:00-22:00.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We offer mentorship, working life balance and professional development opportunities to meet your need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will be involved in direct delivery of care and overseeing nursing care to patients in their own homes and other community settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will be required to work alongside the care coordinator, initiate assessments, develop management plans, implement and evaluate the care of patients on their caseload.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will deliver care to complex patients in the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Catherine DaviesInterim Lead Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;catherine.davies11@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
